ce:section.ce:para:
Uv-vis spectra in Fig. 1
                            of complex 1 shows an intense Soret band at 428 nm accompanied with four less intense red shifted Q bands. A red shift in Soret band was from 428 nm to 432 nm (Table 1
                           ) and four Q bands merged to two on forming complex 2 from complex 1 as expected upon the insertion of central metal [17]. For complex 3, a 4 nm red shifting in the Soret band from 432 nm (for 2) to 436 nm (for 3), Table 1, was observed.

Transmission electron microscopy (TEM) was used for morphological analysis and to estimate the shape, size distribution and particle sizes of FA-NGQDs, 2-FA-NGQDs, and 3-FA-NGQDs. The TEM images (Fig. 3
                           ) for FA-NGQDs showed well defined spherical shapes with an average diameter for 14.27 nm, for 2-FA-NGQDs, and 3-FA-NGQDs the average sizes are 14.69 nm, and 16.10 nm, respectively, Table 2
                           , an increase for all compared to NGQDs at 4.2 nm. A huge increase in size upon the conjugation could be due to aggregation.
